g.text: CPU flags at time of exception

div.p: Stack grows downward Error code popped by IRET (if present, handler must pop it!)
Trigger: DIV or IDIV with divisor = 0 or quotient exceeds destination size
Handler action: Typically SIGFPE to process Can recover by modifying registers and resuming
Trigger: Exception during handler for another exception e.g., Page fault while handling page fault
Handler action: System must reset or halt No recovery possible - state is corrupted
Trigger: Segment limit violation, privileged instruction in user mode, invalid descriptor, writing to RO segment
Trigger: Page not present, privilege violation, reserved bit set, or write to read-only page

ul.li: CR2: Linear address that caused fault
Error code: Tells WHY (P, WR, US bits)

div.p: Common fix: Map page, update permissions, or SIGSEGV
